{
  "stem": "26728.8",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But anyhow, OK, Mauthausen.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We got to Mauthausen on May 5.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it had just been liberated.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We didn't go in until the next day or so.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the General Patton, a tank, I think it was the Fourth Armored Division had liberated Mauthausen.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And when we went in, we were in Linz, in a hotel, and we kept hearing rumors about the war winding down and could be over any day and just scuttlebutt.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were taken into Mauthausen by officers from General Patton's Third Army, and the inmates, for the most part, had already-- what had happened was the SS had abandoned Mauthausen and the Viennese police had taken over Mauthausen.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So when it was liberated, there were very few Germans or Austrians military on premises.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was the Viennese police department that was in charge.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So it was altogether different than any of the other camps.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But it turned out to be, as we learned more about Mauthausen, it turned out to be much worse than any of the other camps that we had seen.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was a whole line of terrible atrocities were perpetrated in Mauthausen.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Mass executions of American POWs, mass executions-- and this is the week before they were liberated-- of Russian POWs.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Mass executions of Spaniards who had been in France.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "After when they had their civil war, whoever lost, I don't know enough about that, had left Spain and gone to France and they had been captured by the Nazis, sent to the camps.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were not Fascists.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I don't know what the hell they were, but the ones that lost the war, the civil war in Spain.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I know that the one that won, that Franco was a Fascist.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Hitler had trained, historically-- it isn't important.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
